Getting Started with NetCI

Welcome to NetCI! Here are some basic tips to get you started:

1. Looking Around
   Type 'look' to see your surroundings and what's in the room.

2. Getting Help
   Type 'help' to see this help system.
   Type 'help commands' to see available commands.
   Type 'help <command>' to get help on a specific command.

3. Talking to Others
   Type 'say <message>' to talk to people in the same room.
   Type 'who' to see who else is online.

4. Moving Around
   Use direction commands like: north, south, east, west, up, down
   (Or their abbreviations: n, s, e, w, u, d)

5. Your Inventory
   Type 'inventory' to see what you're carrying.

6. Exiting
   Type 'quit' when you want to leave.

Have fun exploring!
